    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-09-04T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-09-04T03:00:00-05:00" n="1028"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1028">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.74/1027: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Tientsin</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fletcher</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tientsin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-09-04T17:00:00+09:00"
                            >September 4, 1940—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 4—5 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s 125 [<hi rend="italic">135</hi>], August 29, 4 p.m. to Peiping,
                    Creamer case. Action taken as instructed in paragraph 1 of telegram under
                    reference on August 30. No acknowledgment [as yet?] has been received from the
                    Japanese Consul General, but Creamer yesterday reported that he believed
                    Japanese surveillance of his movements had been discontinued.<note n="80"
                        xml:id="d1028fn80">In despatch No. 1181, September 20, the Consul at
                        Tientsin reported that the Japanese Consul General had replied saying that
                        Mr. Creamer had been placed under surveillance by the military authorities
                        because of his suspected connection with certain “lawless elements”, that
                        the Japanese did not apprehend or question him, and that the surveillance
                        had been withdrawn (893.74/1031).</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sent to Peiping. Repeated to the Department, Chungking. Code text by air mail to
                    Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
